# Shell Script Rules

- Preserve Linux + macOS bash compatibility.
- Prefer extending shared helpers in `scripts/_common.sh` over duplicating logic.
- Keep `setup.sh` and `upgrade.sh` non-destructive by default; never overwrite user config or workspaces unless an explicit sync/cleanup flag is present.
- Do not print secrets, tokens, or full credential-bearing URLs.
- Keep path checks and "refuse unsafe directory" guards intact when touching `OPENCLAW_*` paths.
